  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Suppose I have the following `truffle-config.js` for the sake of spawning a ganache instance that has a specific address that I want:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  networks: {\r\n    develop: {\r\n      fork: process.env.MAINNET_NODE_URL,\r\n      network_id: 1,\r\n      skipDryRun: true,\r\n      accounts: [\r\n        {\r\n          secretKey: process.env.PRIV_KEY,\r\n          balance: ethers.utils.hexlify(ethers.utils.parseEther(\"1000\")),\r\n        },\r\n      ],\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen I run `truffle develop`, it seems like it freezes or it is hanging because the `accounts` property is not being processed properly.\r\n\r\nTake a look at the following code block inside [`develop.js#L56-L58`](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/core/lib/commands/develop.js#L56-L58):\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst { mnemonic, accounts, privateKeys } = mnemonicInfo.getAccountsInfo(\r\n  customConfig.accounts || 10\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\n`customConfig.accounts` is getting passed into `getAccountsInfo()` as if it is a number, but it is actually an array of objects as you can see in the config above. Inside that function, it gets passed as `numAddresses` and is [processed](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/core/lib/mnemonics/mnemonic.js#L41-L56) as if it is a number. This is where the problem lies.",
